# Hacker News Clone

A clone of the popular Hacker News website, built with React.js accesesing the Hacker News API. Users can view the top and most recent news, view user information and comment details.

This application is deployed to Netlify and can be accessed at [To be Added](www.netlify.com)

## Getting Started

These instructions will get you a copy of the project up and running on your local machine for development and testing purposes. See deployment for notes on how to deploy the project on a live system.

### Prerequisites


Clone the repository

Run ```npm install``` from the root of the application,
Run ```npm run start``` to begin the application in development mode


## Built With

* [React](https://reactjs.org/) - JavaScript library for building UI
* [React Router](https://reacttraining.com/react-router/web/guides/quick-start) - Collection of declarative routing components 
* [Webpack](https://webpack.js.org/) - JavaScript module bundler
* [Babel](https://babeljs.io/docs/en/) - JavaScript compiler to make ECMAScript 2015+ code browser compatible
* [query-string](https://www.npmjs.com/package/query-string) - NPM package to parse and stringify URL query strings
* [prop-types](https://www.npmjs.com/package/query-string) - NPM package for runtime type checking for React props


